commit 418f2f245aec87d96ba287b00e2dd590560c9e27
Author: jeeminso <jeeminso@gmail.com>
Date:   Tue Nov 18 22:10:34 2025 -0500

    Fix left-outer-join missing rows when different keys map to the same hash bucket
    
    Left outer joins could skip unmatched rows when distinct keys fell into the
    same hash bucket, because matched state was tracked per hash bucket
    instead of per row.
    
    The fix tracks matched state per row, ensuring that unmatched left-side rows
    are still emitted even when hash buckets contain distinct keys.
    
    Co-authored-by: Sebastian Utz <su@rtme.net>
    (cherry picked from commit d31bd126c49b8283fa5a28b6ec90099024bedef1)

